            <h2>Fix Your Bike</h2>

            <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:14px;">Fix
            Your Bike is our flagship program where anyone can come to our shop
            during designated hours (see below) to utilize our space, tools and
            knowledge to fix their bikes. &nbsp;It is a wonderful opportunity
            to meet your neighbors and others in the community that have a
            common interest in bicycles of all kinds.&nbsp; The music is always
            bumping, the grease a-flying and bike passion burning!&nbsp; We
            welcome everyone, regardless of bike clout, cool factor, gender,
            race, income, etc.&nbsp;</span></p>

            <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:16px;"><em>We
            are</em> <strong>Denverâ€™s Community Bike
            Center!</strong></span></p>

            <p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="" src=
            "/images/Photos/578780_10150653505591150_80966697_n.jpg" style=
            "height: 169px; width: 225px; float: left; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;"><span style="font-size:14px;">You
            do not need prior bicycle knowledge</span><span style=
            "font-size:14px;">, we have Volunteer Mechanics on hand to help
            with your maintenance and repair questions. The help of our
            volunteers is free, but all parts, both new and used, are sold
            separately. &nbsp;As always, Bike Depot Members receive a discount
            on parts and accessories.&nbsp; We have 6 benches, two wheel truing
            stations, a tube patching table and most any specialized tool you
            could want for wrenching bikes.</span></p>

            <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style=
            "font-size:14px;">Volunteer mechanics are there to guide you and
            answer questions, <strong><em>but will not do the work for
            you!</em></strong> &nbsp;If you would like us to service your bike,
            our staff mechanics would gladly do so for our <a href=
            "http://www.thebikedepot.org/betasiteerb/bike-shop/service" target=
            "_blank">standard service rates</a>.</span></p>

            <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

            <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:14px;">All
            participants must sign a waiver before their first visit and sign
            in every subsequent visit.&nbsp;</span></p>

            <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:14px;">There
            is no need to make an appointment, but space is limited and is
            first come, first serve.&nbsp; Participants are not allowed to work
            on their bikes outside of designated Fix Your Bike
            Hours.</span></p>

